<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/23517284-sam"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1559272637i/23517284._UX100_CR0,2,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/23517284-sam">Sam</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Honestly, it depends how old you are. I really really loved them when I was younger (I read them when I was 13), but now at the age 20 I don&apos;t believe<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Honestly, it depends how old you are. I really really loved them when I was younger (I read them when I was 13), but now at the age 20 I don't believe I would like them as much. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
