        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3566709056" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5817362854232654495">Another childhood reread. I got into this around the time I read Harry Potter but HP overshadowed it by alot. I&apos;m pretty sure I&apos;ve been going back to my childhood reads due to the new realizations around Rowling and my disappointment can&apos;t be put to words. So I&apos;m probably searching for other childhood nuggets to fall onto while I go through my pain around HP. <br/><br/>This honestly, is not as exciting as I remember it but it could be the second book that picks up. Most of this is seems to be background a</span>
  <span id="freeText5817362854232654495" style="display:none">Another childhood reread. I got into this around the time I read Harry Potter but HP overshadowed it by alot. I'm pretty sure I've been going back to my childhood reads due to the new realizations around Rowling and my disappointment can't be put to words. So I'm probably searching for other childhood nuggets to fall onto while I go through my pain around HP. <br /><br />This honestly, is not as exciting as I remember it but it could be the second book that picks up. Most of this is seems to be background and setup. I thought I remembered a more exciting setup of the school system but it's pretty simple. The prose is much simpler than other comparable books but I feel the story is more original than the others which I love. Will definitely keep reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5817362854232654495" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
